The paper deals with the development of a fully autonomous swarm-robotics testbed, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of barrier functions for constraint satisfaction and controller synthesis suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). The formulation of robust barrier functions for unmodeled disturbances indicates a concern for system dynamics (cs.SD). Finally, the experimental results showcase the effectiveness of the approach, which could be considered a form of machine learning (cs.LG).
